Atractocerus brasiliensis
is widely distributed throughout the Americas ( Casari and Teixeira 2011 ; Gorham 1881 , 1886 ; Wheeler 1986 ). The distribution of this species in Guatemala and Mexico coincides with the distribution of some host pines ( e.g., Pinus oocarpa Schiede ex Schltdl.) ( Earle 2015 ; Wheeler 1986 ;
Yábar-Landa et al. 2018
), which may be important to understanding their biology.
